  "text": "Dynamic timing analysis determines the effect of different inputs on execution time to approximate the WCET, e.g., to determine that an inversely sorted list maximizes bubblesort's computational complexity. Static analysis bounds aggregate costs of instructions in blocks and then compound the costs of paths throughout the program taking architectural timing effects into account to derive a safe WCET bound at compile time. Static timing analysis has been shown to provide safe WCET bounds [CITATION_1] , much in contrast to the dynamic approach.",
